          "explanation": "Differences b/w Human and Animal hair- Trait Human hair Animal hair General Fine & thin Coarse & thick Cuticle Scales sho, broad, flattened/ thin. Scales large, wavy projections/step-like projections. Coex Thick, 4-10 times as broad as medulla. Thin, rarely more than twice as broad as medulla Medulla Varies, narrow, continuous, fragmented or Absent. Medullary index <1/3 Continuous, wider. Medullary index > 1 / 2 Pigment Evently distributed. Present near the medullar. Precipitin test Specific for human Specific for animal."
