          "explanation": "The picture shows KF ring in eye, a feature of Wilsons disease. * KF ring : Brownish - yellow ring visible around the corneo - sclera junction (limbus) * Consists of copper deposits in Descemet's membrane, extending into the trabecular meshwork * Sign of Wilson's disease * Oral Pencillamine is used in the treatment.",
