          "explanation": "Punishment of revealing the identity of rape victim: If anyone prints or publishes the name or any matter which may reveal the identity of victim of rape, then he is punished with imprisonment for a term up to 2 years and fine (Sec. 228-A IPC). Ref - Krishan Vij textbook of forensic medicine and toxicology 5e , <a href=\" <p>",
