          "explanation": "Dying deposition is a statement of a person on oath, recorded by the Magistrate, in the presence of the accused or his lawyer, who is allowed to cross examine the witness.Not in India. Ref:synopsis of forensic medicine (Dr.K.S.Narayan Reddy) PG NO:7 28th edition",
