          "explanation": "Formic acid is the primary agent responsible for the toxic effects and occular complications. Formaldehyde and formic acid is the single best answer here.\nMethanol is oxidized by the liver to formaldehyde (which is 33 times more toxic than methanol) which in turn is oxidized to formic acid which is sixty times more toxic than methanol and is responsible for the associated metabolic acidosis and retinal toxicity."
