          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "A person born in a lawful marriage is legitimate. If a person is born during the continuance of a legal marriage, or within 280 days after the dissolution of the marriage by divorce or death of the husband, his bih is presumed to be legitimate (S.112, IFA) Ref: Textbook of Forensic Medicine and Toxicology by Narayan Reddy, Edition 21, Page - 335"
