          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Clinical Features of Aconite * Nausea and vomiting * HyperSalivation * Tingling and numbness in mouth and lips * Diarrhea * Palpitation * Weakness * Hypotension * Ventricular ectopics,* Arrhythmias * Veigo * Blurring of vision, hippus, mydriasis, xanthopsia * Convulsions REF;THE SYNOPSIS OF FORENSIC MEDICINE:KS NARAYANA REDDY;28th EDITION;PAGE NO 357",
